    "problemStatement": "Consider an array AAA of length NNN. You know that for all 1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\leq i \\leq N1\u2264i\u2264N, 0\u2264Ai\u22641050 \\leq A_i \\leq 10^50\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264105. We construct an array BBB of length N\u22121N-1N\u22121 such that, for all 1\u2264i\u2264N\u221211 \\leq i \\leq N - 11\u2264i\u2264N\u22121, Bi=min(Ai,Ai+1)B_i = min(A_i, A_{i + 1})Bi\u200b=min(Ai\u200b,Ai+1\u200b).\n\nYou are given the array BBB, you need to find out the total number of distinct arrays AAA which we could have used to construct the given array BBB.\n\nThe answer may be large, so you need to find it modulo 109+710^{9} + 7109+7.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nFirst line will contain TTT, number of testcases. Then the testcases follow.\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer NNN\nThe second line of each test case contains N\u22121N-1N\u22121 space separated integers - the ithi^{th}ith of which is BiB_iBi\u200b\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each testcase(in a new line), output the count of valid possibilities of array AAA modulo 109+710^{9} + 7109+7.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u2264101 \\leq T \\leq 101\u2264T\u226410",
      "2\u2264N\u22641052 \\leq N \\leq 10^52\u2264N\u2264105",
      "0\u2264Bi\u22641050 \\leq B_i \\leq 10^50\u2264Bi\u200b\u2264105"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "3\n2\n100\n5\n3 9 8 4\n3\n10 12",
        "output": "199801\n199983\n199977",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest Case 111: All valid arrays AAA are of the form [100,x][100, x][100,x] and [x,100][x, 100][x,100] where 100\u2264x\u2264105100 \\leq x \\leq 10^5100\u2264x\u2264105. Therefore, the answer is (105\u2212100)+(105\u2212100+1)=199801(10^5 - 100) + (10^5 - 100 + 1) = 199801(105\u2212100)+(105\u2212100+1)=199801.\nTest Case 333: All valid arrays AAA are of the form [10,12,x][10, 12, x][10,12,x] and [10,x,12][10, x, 12][10,x,12] where 12\u2264x\u226410512 \\leq x \\leq 10^512\u2264x\u2264105. Therefore, the answer is (105\u221212)+(105\u221212+1)=199977(10^5 - 12) + (10^5 - 12 + 1) = 199977(105\u221212)+(105\u221212+1)=199977."
      }
    ]
